item.description: The annual Schnitzelfest is scheduled for September 29th from 12 noon to 5pm in Hillsborough NH. There will be food(schnitzel, bratwurst, weiners, desserts, beer, etc) and German music, items for sale(Christmas presents?). There are antique shops, historical bldgs., arched stone bridges, German John's Bakery, a library that used to be a NH governor's home and Foodees Pizza started here. I haven't been to this event yet but have been trying to get there for several years. It is a nice ride on back roads to get to Hillsborough and it is an interesting town.(603-432-4271)
